# MCP Server Tools

## Tool design

- Define tools with `server.tool(name, description, zodSchema, handler)`
- Use clear zod `.describe()` on every parameter
- Return `{ content: [{ type: 'text', text: string }] }` — JSON-stringify structured payloads

## Existing tools

| Tool | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `scan_page` | Scan browser via `cdpEndpoint` or `wsEndpoint`; writes `registry/{scanName}.json` |
| `get_registry` | Full registry JSON (high token cost) |
| `get_registry_keys` | Lightweight key list (prefer this first) |
| `get_locator` | Single entry by key |
| `search_registry` | Filter by tagName, testId, text, confidence |
| `list_registries` | List available registry files |

## scan_page

- Requires exactly one of `cdpEndpoint` or `wsEndpoint`
- `scanMode`: `interactive` (default), `testId`, or `full`
- On success, include `registryFile`, stats, and guidance to use token-efficient read tools

## Error responses

Return plain-text errors in `content[0].text` — include actionable setup hints (e.g. Chrome `--remote-debugging-port`).
